Phenomenon 60.description:
The Default Room, also known as Phenomenon 60, is an anomalous location or phenomenon that occurs when new levels are characterised by instability, causing cube-shaped rooms to glitch out and be replaced by The Void or the Default Room. However, these rooms are temporary and dissipate within a few minutes, replaced by the level's intended design. In rarer cases, one can be transported into the room directly when noclipping to a new level; however, they will teleport into the intended level minutes later.

The Default Room's appearance is minimal: an indestructible white drywall room encompassing a fireplace in a corner - the chimney blocked off, and a locked glass door with a blindingly bright light. As a phenomenon, one of the walls will demanifest to serve as an entrance or exit. Additional features, such as the arbitrarily functional outlets and a nylon beige carpet, are the only things that are destructible.

The Default Room does not exhibit the properties nor effects of the level it is in. As a result, a default room could serve as a temporary resting area in unsafe conditions, although entities can still barge in. The Default Room's singular properties are minimal. Hydration and starvation are mostly void, if not absent; the carpet is unable to absorb liquid, and noclipping is not possible.

It is theorised that the Default Room had been a popular level in the past, with past (~2005) reports describing a somewhat similar, though complex description of it more akin to that of a level. Nonetheless, after reports died down then rose again in 2007, further descriptions described the present-day appearance of the Default Room. This is yet a theory as past reports are unreliable due to their vagueness, and the fact attributed writers do not remember writing such a report. Such an event has been previously observed in the old Level 13, wherein wanderers had their memories forgotten or replaced, attributed to the level.

It is unknown if it is truly a standalone location. Due to the Default Room's temporary nature akin to a phenomenon, only being replaced with the actual level in minutes, and as a standalone location which teleports you to the intended level within minutes, it is unknown if this standalone location is outside the level or is a replacement of the level.
> The grandiose art of erosion;
> The thing that places in the nock-and-crannies of your mind;
> To be now forgotten;
> Existence now simplified;
> An identity overwritten.

